{{Alt Class 2|entity=1|no=612|environment=3|exit=4}}

<div style="margin:1em; font-size:17px; text-align:center">{{Underline|ffbdbd}}'''Level 612''', also known as "''Heartbreak''" or "''HeartSever''" is the '''613th''' level in the backrooms. 
{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
<div class="header" style="background: rgba(170, 51, 106,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="8">Description</font></div>
{{Blurimage|file=5c7286e8d32018821f42f9daafd38375.jpg|hovertext=Congratulations on your marriage!|caption=The first room.|align=Center}}{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
<Div style="margin-left: 2em;margin-right: 2em;">Level 612 manifests as a room littered with flowers and cakes, with nobody around; celebratory music playing regardless of where the wanderer is located. The walls are painted pink and white, with perfume and the faint smell of smoke filling the air. Chandeliers are common within the level, though most are either broken or have no power flowing to them. Despite this, light is still present with no visible source. Most walls contain lead-based paint, leading researchers to believe that this level was created during the 1800's. Rooms within Level '''612''' typically vary in size, most being 150 to 421 square feet. Basic furniture, such as dressers or tables, are typically made out of cherry wood and covered in flowers, usually being blue or pink; or surrounded by balloons. 

One may find gifts lying on the tables, which cannot be opened, no matter how hard one tries. However, gifts can be cut or split open; most gifts contain [[Object 1]] or [[Object 2|Level Keys]]. According to [[M.E.G.]] researchers, gifts will contain [[Object 2|Level Keys]] to: [[Level 414]], [[Level 111]], [[Level 333]], [[Level 997]], and [[Level 667]]. As of current, no other [[Object 2|Level Keys]] have been found. Tables may also have half eaten cakes or alcoholic beverages. For unknown reasons, most '''wine bottles''' are shattered; believed to be due to the personal beliefs of '''John Doe.'''


No other phenomena have been observed within this section of the level.  </div>
{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
<div class="header" style="background: rgba(170, 51, 106,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3.1px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="8">Sanctuary</font></div>
{{Blurimage|file=Screenshot 2025-09-07 12.47.18 PM.png|caption=A wanderer running from the flames within the sanctuary, presumably created by '''John Doe.'''|align=Center}}{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
<Div style="margin-left: 2em;margin-right: 2em;">The Sanctuary is approximately 4 miles (or 6.437km) from the first room, charred and covered in lead dust. It consists of dining tables, most being circular or diamond-shaped, and aligned in certain patterns; diamond tables may be aligned in a triangle-like structure, whereas circular tables may be aligned in a square-like structure.  Tables also have candles and flowers placed onto them, candles being contained within a glass container, whilst flowers are contained within a plastic cup, usually without soil or water; most flowers are wilted or are on fire due to the flames.

Chairs within the area are interconnected, having a width of 6 feet and a length of 3 feet, also being presumed to be the main cause of the fire within the Sanctuary, due to the few chairs not on fire having gasoline poured onto them. The walls are made of cobblestone, which are chipped and cracked, presumably by '''John Doe''' or external sources.  The "Sanctuary" is naturally permeated by an orange glow, caused by the flames within the section, by extension, no known method can extinguish these fires; as they reignite instantly when put out. Due to this, the flames will gradually spread throughout the level, engulfing the first area, whilst infinitely spreading through The Honeymoon Suite.            

Due to the amount of smoke in the Sanctuary, the area has a extremely high probability of lung cancer, respiratory and cardiovascular issues, asphyxiation, pneumonitis, heart attacks, and Methemoglobinemia due to inhalation of smoke. 


Due to the nature of this section, no other information is obtainable. </div>
{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
<div class="titleblock">
<span class="titlebox">Recovered Log</span><br>
<center>''Captured by a wanderer which happened to be present at the time to witness the scene.''</center><br>
<div style="font-family: Courier; margin:1em; font-size:20px; text-align:center">

Sarah: "W-What do you get out of this? Is it fun to you or s-something?

John Doe: "..."

Sarah: "S-Say something, dammit!"

John Doe: "...can you shut the HELL UP? Why do you keep fucking following me, Sarah? You already know damn well that those [[M.E.G.|idiots]] tried to get you! Go with them for gods sake, you'd be better off with them than me!"

Sarah: "I don't care about those [[M.E.G.|creeps]]! I just... I... B-Because I wanna k-know w-why you're doing this! W-Whats the point?"

John Doe: "Sigh... Because I'm crazy. Now leave before I burn you too."

''Sarah takes a step back.''

Sarah: "B-But still... there has to be some motivation for this! You can't just be crazy! There has to be some reason for WHY you're doing this... and, where is-"

John Doe: "Like I said, I'm crazy."

Sarah: "I-I meant, what made you crazy... and, why did you cut me off, what happened to-"

John Doe: "...and why do you wanna know so bad?"

Sarah: "M-Maybe because you're lighting everything on fire?? And he-"

John Doe: "Whatever. I just don't like this place; and if I don't like it, i'm burning it."

Sarah: "I hate this place too! But that doesn't mean you make this place more dangerous than it already is! A-And I'm just gonna give up on asking..."

John Doe: "What danger is there to be if theirs nothing left to threaten us?"

Sarah: "Are you an idiot? You're starting a fire! That's gonna threaten us!"

John Doe: "It'll be put out by those M.E.G. guys."

Sarah: "This place isn't even documented yet!"

John Doe: "And...? They'll find it."

Sarah: "I swear... what fucking happened to you?"

John Doe: "I just told you earlier that I don't like this place, so I'm burning it."

Sarah: "Do you not care about living?"

John Doe: "Of course I care about keeping myself alive-"

Sarah: "THEN WHY THE HELL ARE YOU LIGHTING THIS PLACE ON FIRE? THERE WAS NOTHING HERE, NOTHING TO HURT US, AND YET YOU JUST BURN EVERYTHING! YOU'RE THE ONE MAKING THIS PLACE DANGEROUS!"

''John Doe just smiles.''

John Doe: "I don't like it. And I know I'll get out anyway. Plus, didn't we just see a smiler?"

Sarah: "...y-you aren't crazy, you're just stupid."

John Doe: "Nuh uh."

''Sarah loses her patience.''

Sarah: "WE CAN BOTH DIE IN THIS FIRE! STOP! WE ALREADY-"

John Doe: {{Wavy|text="...you just made me want to keep going."}}

<code>End of Log</code>
</div>
</div>
John Doe constantly ignores questions about a certain individual or organism, which many point to as why John Doe is destroying the environment and qualities of levels. The wanderer which captured this exchange stated that Sarah followed John Doe across the level; constantly questioning, "What is wrong with you?"
{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
<div class="header" style="background: rgba(170, 51, 106,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="8">Honeymoon Suite</font></div>
{{Blurimage|file=Awwww.webp|caption=A image of the Honeymoon Suite, the curtain automatically rolled up. Name of said photographer is unknown; presumed to be Sarah or John Doe.|align=Center}}{{Blurimage|file=SuiteSuiteSuiteSuiteSuiteSarahSuiteSuiteSuiteSuiteJohnDoeSuiteSuiteSuiteSuiteTravelSuiteSuite.webp|caption=Another section within "The Honeymoon Suite". Unlike other sections, this section does not have the "Valentines Day" aesthetic.}}{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
<Div style="margin-left: 2em;margin-right: 2em;">
The Honeymoon Suite is an infinitely expanding resimercial space with non-Euclidean geometry, mostly decorated in a Valentine's day aesthetic. The Honeymoon Suite defies the laws of physics in multiple ways; if one were to walk into a section blocked off by a curtain said curtain will automatically roll up and let the wanderer through, with no visible mechanism to lift the curtain up. If one were to touch these curtains during their rolled-up state, they behave as if they are not bound by the effects of gravity.       

The Honeymoon Suite's architecture is typically the main danger; as a resimercial space, the "levels attempt" to blend domestic and corporate fail. As such, literal errors in the design are present. For example, a minibar in a domestic space may be split in half by a white wall, or a doorway leads to a six foot drop into a office.  Certain areas of The Honeymoon Suite often loop back into themselves and or previous areas. Because of this, fire is gradually spreading within The Honeymoon Suite due to the flames from the Sanctuary. The Honeymoon Suite presumably is located in [[Level 398|The Frontrooms]], as outside of the windows appears to be [[Level 398|Earth]]. One can break these windows and jump out to re-enter [[Level 398|The Frontrooms.]] However, this is ill-advised, as jumping out of these windows presumably leads to a '''24 mile fall''', which is unsurvivable unless one has some [[Object List|Object]] to prevent said falls(e.g. parachutes). 

The Honeymoon Suite can also loop back into other levels; for example, the structure could loop into [[Level 111]] and then back into itself. Oddly, this does not provide an exit, as any "exit" manifested in a level will automatically lead back to The Honeymoon Suite.  Due to the lack of a coherent structure, one traveling through this section of Level 612 will experience disorientation and or fear.   

No other phenomena have been observed within "The Honeymoon Suite". 
{{Underline|ffbdbd}}
=== Entities ===
There is a minimal entity presence, as most either perished in the fire or died of air quality. Entities include [[Entity 8|Hounds]], [[Entity 9|Facelings]], and rarely, [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]]. 

=== Outposts ===
Due to the nature of this level, no outposts have been established.
=== Entrances ===
Burning an entity alive with [[Object 15]] has a ''small chance'' to bring you here.

Experiencing a breakup or any negative love-related event based on romance has a ''small chance'' to bring you here.

Burning a blue flower in [[Level 111]] ''may'' bring you here.

Staying within '''The Faint Halls''' in [[Level 997]] for an ''unknown period of time'' will bring you here.


=== Exits ===
Exiting this level is significantly more challenging than it used to be, as multiple exits have been blocked off or require [[Object 2|Level Keys]],  However, the current remaining exits which do not include [[Object 2|Level Keys]] and are not blocked off include:

Experiencing a positive love-related event based on romance transports one to [[Level 9]].

Breaking any of the windows in the Honeymoon Suite and jumping out of it causes you to fall 24 miles to [[Level 398|Reality.]] 

